JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 104
EP  - 118
VL  - 26
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Two laboratory experiments examined the role of causal attributions as the cognitive component in Locke's (1968) model of goal setting. Environmental incentives were found to be subject to causal interpretation but not to affect goal aspirations per se. A strong interaction between environmental incentives and causal attributions on goal aspirations was found.
AB  - Two laboratory experiments examined the role of causal attributions as the cognitive component in Locke's (1968) model of goal setting. Environmental incentives were found to be subject to causal interpretation but not to affect goal aspirations per se. A strong interaction between environmental incentives and causal attributions on goal aspirations was found.
